    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nHi, for some reason Pyright is not working on my neovim at all, all the other LSPs I use are working, it was working and in the same day it stop doing so.\r\n\r\nI tested with a minimal configuration, tested with neovim's stable release, tested in neovim nightly, all of these gives me the same output: All the LSPs are working, except by Pyright.\r\n\r\nThe LSP gets attached with the lsp-config.nvim, but none of its functionality works, the completion I set doesn't work; holding down TAB (the key I choose to toggle on completion + to browse through the options), I lose control over the cursor and have to use my mouse to click on neovim's window to regain it.\r\n\r\nUsing the minimal_init.lua configuration with any language servers works, except by Pyright, it returns the following:\r\n```\r\nSpawning language server with cmd: `pyright-langserver --stdio` failed. The language server is either not installed, missing from PATH, or not executable.\r\n```\r\nI have `pyright-langserver` in my PATH, I can use this command on a terminal.\r\nI tested the `pyright` on terminal and it worked.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\r\n\r\n```\r\nlocal pattern = 'python'\r\nlocal cmd = {'pyright-langserver --stdio'}\r\n-- Add files/folders here that indicate the root of a project\r\nlocal root_markers = {'.git', '.editorconfig'}\r\n-- Change to table with settings if required\r\nlocal settings = vim.empty_dict()\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\r\n  pattern = pattern,\r\n  callback = function(args)\r\n    local match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\r\n    local root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, ':p:h') or nil\r\n    vim.lsp.start({\r\n      name = 'bugged-ls',\r\n      cmd = cmd,\r\n      root_dir = root_dir,\r\n      settings = settings\r\n    })\r\n  end\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWork.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.4\r\n\r\n### Language server name/version\r\n\r\npyright 1.1.340\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux 6.6.7-zen1-1-zen x86_64\r\n\r\n### Log file\r\n\r\n_No response_",
